qas.question: When did the first free election take place?
What was different about later elections then first free election?

answers.text: no restrictions on the choice of candidates.

qas.question: Who only voted in the election of 1492?
What dynasty was in reign during the election of 1492?

context: The first "free election" (Polish: "wolna elekcja") of a king took place in <a0_0>1492<a0_0/>. (To be sure, some earlier Polish kings had been elected with help from bodies such as that which put Casimir II on the throne, thereby setting a precedent for free elections.) Only <a2_0>senators<a2_0/> voted in the 1492 free election, which was won by <a3_0>John I Albert<a3_0/>. For the duration of the <a4_0>Jagiellonian Dynasty<a4_0/>, only members of that royal family were considered for election; later, there would be <a1_0>no restrictions on the choice of candidates.
